<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53122ac"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53122ac">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53122ac"> 122(ac)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> he met old man, / sick old bankrupt, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53122ac"><li>FW 24.22 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n53122ac">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n53122ac">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53122ac">MS BL 47476a-149</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:321 <a name="ad7" href="../../FF/fdra/ada.htm#ad7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad7.htm#n53122ac">Draft: I.1&sect;1.7</a>/2.7</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Alors, les Dieux, jaloux de la f&eacute;licit&eacute; c&eacute;leste que go&ucirc;tait une ville de la terre, form&egrave;rent <mark>un vieillard</mark>, et renvoy&egrave;rent <mark>sur le chemin du prince</mark>, pour troubler son esprit. <p>L&apos;h&ocirc;mme s&apos;appuyait sur un b&acirc;ton: il &eacute;tait <mark>d&eacute;cr&eacute;pit, cass&eacute;</mark>. Les veines saillaient sur son corps, les dents branlaient dans sa bouche, sa peau &eacute;tait toute creus&eacute;e de rides noires; de son cr&acirc;ne pendaient quelques cheveux d&apos;un gris sale; ses paupi&egrave;res, sans cils, &eacute;taient rouges; sa t&ecirc;te, ses jambes, ses bras tremblaient.</p> <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 42</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: On one trip so, Siddharta met the Deva in the guise of an old man and thus learned of old age. On another time he met the Deva as a sick man and thus learned of sickness, of suffering and disease. On a third occasion, the Deva appeared before him in the semblance of a corpse and thus the prince learned of death itself.</mm> </dd></dl>
